items.title: Uncertainty over economy, tariffs forces retailers to be cautious on holiday hiring
items.description: Rising tariff costs and other economic factors are forcing retailers to pull back or even delay their plans to hire seasonal workers

items.title: China shows no sign of backing down; calls for US to withdraw tariff threat
items.description: China has called for the U.S. to withdraw a new threat of a 100% tariff and other export control measures

items.title: Fast trains collide in Slovakia, injuring dozens, with 2 in critical condition
items.description: Two fast trains have collided in eastern Slovakia, injuring dozens of passengers

items.title: Nobel economics prize goes to 3 for explaining innovation-driven economic growth
items.description: Joel Mokyr, Philippe Aghion and Peter Howitt have won the Nobel memorial prize in economics for explaining innovation-driven economic growth
